<FIRST>r a AM-ChildAbuse     02-13 0176</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Child Abuse,0181</SECOND>
<HEAD>Malnourished And Badly Battered Child Found On Subway; Parents Charged</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A couple who reported their 7-year-old son
missing were charged Monday with child abuse after the bruised and
malnourished boy was found on a subway car with cigarette burns and
black eyes, police said.
   Rene Samacarit, 28, and Zorida Maldonado, 31, of Brooklyn were
charged with second-degree assault and endangering the welfare of a
minor, said police spokesman Sgt. Raymond O'Donnell.
   The couple reported the boy missing at 2:30 p.m. Less than half
an hour later, Transit Police found the malnourished and beaten
child on a subway in Manhattan, O'Donnell said.
   The boy, who had run away from home, was taken to St. Vincent's
Hospital with multiple injuries, including cigarette burns, bruises,
black eyes, a throat infection and malnutrition, O'Donnell said.
   His parents identified him at the hospital and were charged
following an investigation, O'Donnell said.
   The boy's 3-year-old sister has been turned over to the Bureau of
Child Welfare, O'Donnell said.
   The children's names were not released.
</TEXT>
