<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   With 14 seconds left in his 18th and final
National Basketball Association All-Star Game, Kareem Abdul-Jabbar
finally hit a sky hook.
   After missing five sky hooks, he made his sixth to score the
West's final field goal in its 143-134 victory over the East on
Sunday.
   ``I would have been disappointed if it hadn't dropped,'' said the
41-year-old Los Angeles Laker center, who is retiring at the end of
the season, his 20th season. ``I wanted to get a field goal.''
   Abdul-Jabbar was able to play in the game because of an injury to
teammate Magic Johnson.
