<HEAD>Freeway Ramps Temporarily Closed For Sheep Crossing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CALABASAS, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Up to 1,000 sheep being escorted across
the Ventura Freeway prompted a 30-minute closure of some exit ramps
on the highway, police said.
   California Highway Patrol officers early Sunday diverted traffic
from the Las Virgenes Road ramps as the sheep were escorted over a
bridge from the north side of the freeway to the south, dispatcher
