<FIRST>r a PM-People-Caan-Crash     02-13 0200</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-People-Caan-Crash,0211</SECOND>
<HEAD>James Caan Crashes On Motorcycle, Suffers Broken Ribs</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTA MONICA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actor James Caan suffered broken ribs
after he lost control of his motorcycle and it crashed, police said.
   Caan, 49, wasn't wearing a helmet but suffered no serious head
injuries in the crash, which occurred shortly before noon Sunday,
said police Lt. Barney Melekian.
   The crash were under investigation, but there were no sign that
Caan was intoxicated, Melekian said. Weather conditions were clear
and no other vehicles were involved.
   Besides fractured ribs, the actor suffered minor facial cuts and
bruises, said Corinne Rogers, nursing supervisor at St. Johns
Hospital and Medical Center, where Caan was listed in good condition.
   Caan played Sonny Corleone, the hot-headed son of the Mafia
chieftain in the Oscar-winning film ``The Godfather,'' and portrayed
terminally ill Chicago Bears football running back Brian Piccolo in
the TV movie ``Brian's Song.''
   His other credits include ``Rollerball,'' ``Cinderella Liberty,''
``A Bridge Too Far,'' ``Freebie and the Bean'' and ``Rabbit Run.''
   The crash came two months after actor Gary Busey crashed his
Harley-Davidson while riding without a helmet.
   He suffered serious head injuries but is improving.
   Like Busey, Caan was riding a Harley.
</TEXT>
