<FIRST>r i PM-Iran-Hangings     02-13 0167</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Iran-Hangings,0173</SECOND>
<HEAD>Iran To Hang 70 People Convicted of Drug Smuggling</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Iran on Tuesday will hang 70 people
convicted of drug trafficking, the Islamic Republic News Agency
reported.
   The previous record for drug-related executions was 56 people
hanged on Jan. 16.
   Iran instituted harsh drug laws on Jan. 21 mandating death for
anyone found with more than an ounce of heroin or over 11 pounds of
opium or hashish.
   Up to 1 million of Iran's 47 million people are drug addicts.
   The IRNA report, monitored in Nicosia, said 10 convicts will go
to the gallows in Tehran and the others in eight provincial capitals
and 17 smaller towns.
   Iran suspended executions during celebrations Feb. 1-10 of the
10th anniversary of the 1979 Islamic revolution.
   In a related statement, police in Tehran announced today they
have arrested 3,300 drug traffickers since 1987. During the same
period, police said they seized 10.78 tons of opium, 1,540 pounds of
heroin and 2.25 tons of hashish.
</TEXT>
