<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--HospitalShooting     02-13 0203</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Hospital Shooting,0207</SECOND>
<HEAD>Reputed Crime Figure Killed in Hospital</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MESAGNE, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two masked gunmen sneaked into a hospital
early Monday and killed a reputed crime figure in his bed, where he
was recovering from an assassination attempt two days earlier,
police said.
   Patients and hospital employees dived for cover under beds when
the gunmen opened fire in the public hospital in Mesagne, a town of
30,000 people near Brindisi in the southern Apulia region, according
to the news agency AGI.
   The victim, Antonio Antonica, 31, had been admitted Saturday
night after two masked gunmen shot him outside his home. He suffered
a hand wound and asked to be hospitalized for his own safety.
   The assassins entered the hospital at dawn, made their way to the
orthopedic ward on the second floor and subdued the doctor on duty,
police said.
   They burst into Antonica's room, which he shared with two other
patients, shot him twice in the neck and escaped in the ensuing
panic, police said.
   Investigators said the killing apparently stemmed from a war
between rival criminal gangs for control of the drug trafficking
trade in the region. They said Antonica had been arrested previously
on charges of criminal association.
</TEXT>
