<HEAD>Police Kill A Leader Of Group Blamed For Sadat's Death</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CAIRO, Egypt (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police on Monday killed an alleged Moslem
fundamentalist leader of the outlawed Jihad organization, which was
blamed for killing President Anwar Sadat in 1981 and a failed coup
attempt, police said.
   A police source said on condition of anonymity that Maged
Mohammed Oteify was shot Monday night on a busy downtown street.
   The source said Oteify, 35, was a Jihad leader who had eluded
