assassination, 17 others were given prison terms and two were
acquitted.
   In a later trial, 300 Jihad members were accused of trying to
overthrow the government after the assassination. The court
sentenced 107 to various prison sentences, but acquitted the rest.
Egyptian officials said 87 people, including 66 policemen, were
killed in the attempted coup.
