<HEAD>Coast Guard Picks up 141 Haitians Off Bahamas</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A sailboat carrying 141 Haitians was intercepted
Monday by a U.S. Coast Guard cutter off Great Inagua Island in the
Bahamas.
   The Coast Guard said the cutter Dependable took the refugees off
the 45-foot boat and is holding them until immigration officials
determine whether to return them to their homeland.
   None of the Haitians were reported to have serious health
problems, said Coast Guard spokesman Jerry Snyder.
   Most Haitians are returned to Haiti unless they indicate they
have a fear of political persecution, immigration officials say.
