<FIRST>r i AM-Peru-Violence     02-13 0114</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Peru-Violence,0118</SECOND>
<HEAD>Suspected Leftist Guerrillas Shoot And Kill Mayor</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HUANCAYO, Peru (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Suspected leftist guerrillas on Monday
assassinated the mayor of an Andean town, police said.
   Police quoted residents of San Jose de Quero as saying about 15
armed and hooded guerrillas broke into the home of Mayor Maaximo
Clemente Cairo and led him into the street, where two of the gunmen
shot and killed him.
   Clemente Cairo, 33, was a member of the center-left Aprista Party
led by President Alan Garcia.
   The town, 125 miles east of Lima, is in a region that has seen
activity by the Maoist group Shining Path and the pro-Castro Tupac
Amaru Revolutionary Movement, police said.
</TEXT>
