<SECOND>AM-IBM-Software,0130</SECOND>
<HEAD>IBM Opens, Expands Offices For Software Development</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   International Business Machines Corp. said Monday
it is expanding or creating software development offices in
Charlotte, N.C.; Manassas, Va.; and Endicott and Owego, N.Y.
   IBM said about 2,000 to 2,200 people would be hired, transferred
or given new assignments in the reorganization, which will be
completed by the end of 1989.
   The programs that will be developed will be tailored to the needs
of particular businesses such as banking, financing and
manufacturing.
   In addition, IBM said the workstation printer development work
that is done in Charlotte will be moved to IBM's laboratory in
Lexington, Ky., where most workstation printers are manufactured.
Employees will be offered jobs in the new location.
