<SECOND>AM-Hertz-Mobile Phones,0162</SECOND>
<HEAD>Hertz To Offer Mobile Phones With Credit Card Readers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Hertz Corp. said Monday it will offer phones
activated by credit cards in its rental cars in four test cities.
   The credit-card phones will be supplied by GTE Cellular
Communications Corp. and will be offered in Oklahoma City, Dallas,
St. Louis and Hartford, Conn., Hertz said.
   The other major car rental companies also offer cellular phones
in selected cities, but Hertz spokesman Joseph M. Russo said he
believed Hertz was the first one to offer cellular phones that have
slots to accept credit cards.
   Other car rental companies charge for use of their mobile phones
by keeping track of the calls that are made from the phone number
assigned to a customer.
   Charges for the Hertz phones are billed directly to the
customer's credit card.
   Hertz also said it will offer portable phones at 14 rental
locations nationwide.
</TEXT>
